# Contract Hardening Strategy
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Streaming (Pub/Sub)
  - Proto schema enforcement at topic level
  - Dead-letter queues for schema violations
  - Automated schema evolution checks in CI
  - Real-time validation dashboards

@col:
  ## Table-Based (BigQuery)
  - dbt contracts on all gold-layer models
  - Column-level lineage via dbt metadata
  - Automated freshness + volume anomaly alerts
  - Schema change approval workflow

@notes: The key insight is that streaming and batch need different
contract strategies. Pub/Sub gets proto-first enforcement, BigQuery
gets dbt-native contracts. One size doesn't fit all.

